com.cyc.baseclient.inference

Class KBQueryFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.inference.KBQueryFactory

  • public class KBQueryFactory
extends Object
    KBQueryFactory provides factory methods for inference workers where the query information--the sentence, the ELMt and the inference parameters-- are backed by a KBQ term in the CYC knowledge base.

      • getInferenceWorker

        public InferenceWorker getInferenceWorker(CycAccess access,
                                 DenotationalTerm kbq,
                                 long timeoutMsecs,
                                 boolean sync)
                                   throws CycApiException,
                                          CycConnectionException
        Create a new instance of InferenceWorker, either synchronous or asynchronous, that will run the query in the ELMt and with the parameters specified by the CYC query in the Cyc KB and uniquely denoted by the KBQ parameter.
        Parameters:
        access - the CycAccess object that specifies the CYC server that hosts the reified query and that will perform the inference (i.e. to which the inference worker is bound)
        kbq - the Cyc term that specifies the query
        timeoutMsecs - the timeout parameter for the inference worker in milli-seconds
        sync - if true, returns an instance of DefaultInferenceWorkerSynch; otherwise an instance of DefaultInferenceWorker
        Returns:
        an instance of DefaultInferenceWorker, either synchronized or not, depending on the value of sync
        Throws:
        IOException - if the converse operation throws an IOException
        CycApiException - if the converse operation throws a CycApiException
        CycConnectionException

      • getInferenceWorkerWithSubstitutions

        public InferenceWorker getInferenceWorkerWithSubstitutions(CycAccess access,
                                                  DenotationalTerm kbq,
                                                  Map<CycVariableImpl,Object> substitutions,
                                                  long timeoutMsecs,
                                                  boolean sync)
                                                    throws CycApiException,
                                                           CycConnectionException
        Create a new instance of InferenceWorker, either synchronous or asynchronous, that will run the query in the ELMt and with the parameters specified by the CYC query in the Cyc KB and uniquely denoted by the KBQ parameter. After the query sentence has been loaded, apply the substitutions spelled out in the substitution map, equating variables with bindings.
        Parameters:
        access - the CycAccess object that specifies the CYC server that hosts the reified query and that will perform the inference (i.e. to which the inference worker is bound)
        kbq - the Cyc term that specifies the query
        substitutions - a mapping from CycVariableImpl to Objects; each mapping is converted into an equalSymbols clause and conjoined to the query sentence
        timeoutMsecs - the timeout parameter for the inference worker in milli-seconds
        sync - if true, returns an instance of DefaultInferenceWorkerSynch; otherwise an instance of DefaultInferenceWorker
        Returns:
        an instance of DefaultInferenceWorker, either synchronized or not, depending on the value of sync
        Throws:
        IOException - if the converse operation throws an IOException
        CycApiException - if the converse operation throws a CycApiException
        CycConnectionException
